The paper deals with graph sparsification, which is a topic in graph algorithms and data structures. The use of edge connectivity and spanning trees suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The construction of sparsifiers may also be relevant to computational geometry, which falls under cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of Karger's contraction algorithm suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
